cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you reference this research program or its artifacts, please cite it as follows."
title: "The Modeling Bench — A Three-Paper Research Program in Applied Linear Algebra and CS Education"
abstract: >-
  A mentee-led research program planning and executing three first-author
  papers at the intersection of applied linear algebra, hands-on lab pedagogy,
  and CS education in the age of AI. All three papers deliberately extend
  written invitations from Jeff Anderson's published work at Foothill College.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Fan"
    given-names: "Henry"
    affiliation: "Foothill–De Anza Community College District"
    website: "https://fansofhenry.github.io"
  # Jeff Anderson is listed as research mentor and second author on every
  # paper in the program. The CFF schema has no explicit "role" field, so
  # the relationship is documented here in a comment and on the lab page.
  - family-names: "Anderson"
    given-names: "Jeff"
    affiliation: "Foothill College"
repository-code: "https://github.com/fansofhenry/fansofhenry.github.io"
url: "https://fansofhenry.github.io/research-lab/"
keywords:
  - "CS education"
  - "linear algebra pedagogy"
  - "hands-on laboratory kits"
  - "mathematical modeling"
  - "AI tutoring"
  - "anti-racist learning objectives"
  - "community college"
license: "CC-BY-4.0"
